==> TOPIC:  IDENTIFY YOURSELF FIRST!

From:  David Leonhardt <amabaie@phastnet.com>

Marcia Yudkin wrote:
>> Being forced to select an identifier prior to choosing products
makes me very suspicious that the price will be different depending
on what I say, or that some products may not be shown to me at all,
based on the corporation's stereotype of what customers in different
classifications need. <<

I so agree with this statement.  What I find even more irritating is
when I want to get a quick price quote and have to fill in
everything from my name and address to my second cousin's favorite
ice cream flavor.  I am rarely ready to buy until I have done proper
research, and I often will leave a web site when the "irritation
factor" of form filling gets too high.

For that reason, I ensure that price and format of my products is up
front. I'll do business with someone I trust; I expect people will
do business with me if I am up front with them.

David Leonhardt
The Happy Guy http://www.TheHappyGuy.com
 Kick-start your day with "Your Daily Dose of Happiness"
http://www.TheHappyGuy.com/daily-happiness-free-ezine.html

